<br>
1) Druid pets have recieved a damage nerf that lowers their ability to hold agro.  As a result, Druids who depend heavily on their pets while soloing are finding it much harder to play.<br>
<br>
2) Archers took a substantial hit to their accuracy and damage.  Damage has been decreased by about 10% and the  miss ratio has been increased dramatically for blues and yellows (orange+ is now almost impossible to hit at all)<br>
<br>
Both of these changes were unanounced.  furthermore, when brought to Mythics attention, Sanya posted that she wanted archers to post feedback regarding the problems they were having. (no mention at all of Druid pets)  Oaklief, the Scout team leader, was emailed by Mythic management regarding the patch, and was told that this is a bug and to please investigate.  Monday rolls around, Sanya reports that "some of these latest changes will be undone" but with no ETA. Archers feel uneasy because Sanya is so vague in her post.  On tuesday, Sanya proclaims that the changes are here to stay, because an unnamed archer was able to solo a red <I>player</I> in RVR...<br>
<br>
So heres my dilema... I have a druid who can't solo worth beans now.  I also have an Archer who suddenly has trouble soloing blues. (even though somebody told sanya that we can solo reds *sigh* probably a jealous eldritch)  I'm very very unimpressed with Mythics actions through this past week (Sanya totally reminded me of Abashi, and thats a bad bad thing - she's never been vague before)<br>
<br>
I never really get a whole lot of time to play anyway, but when I did I liked the fact that I could solo decently well with either of my characters...  Now I'm starting to think that Curling up with a good book > playing nerfed classes in Camelot...<br>
<br>
