Good idea in theory, but impossible in practice.  You can't perfectly balance a game when it's at ~5% capacity and out of that 5%, only 10% are actually beta testing.  :) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/unyssarainwhisper.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nyssa Rainwhisper</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://arnemetia.homestead.com/files/MiscImages/bluepawbullet.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(11/21/01 6:30:31 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://arnemetia.homestead.com/files/DAoC/lynxhead.jpg WIDTH=115 HEIGHT=116></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Really mad at Mythic &amp; Sanya over latest patch</span><hr size=1> Tudamorf says: <i><b>Why is the timing of the announcement so important? The nerf would still be there, and your gameplay would be affected in exactly the same way. Does a few days' notice matter so much?</i></b><br>
<br>
Sure a few days' notice won't change anything, but I think what might have annoyed Salicia about that is the fact that it was suddenly sprung on us.  We didn't see it coming.  She logged on one day playing the way she always have been, then the next, her usual technique that she had grown accustomed to, simply failed on her.  At least with a few days' warning she could've braced herself, and plan accordingly.  Sure nerfing and dying are a regular parts of MMORPGs, but I don't think it's much to ask from a company who prides themselves on superb customer service to announce a "change."  Do you?<br>
<br>
Mythic prides themselves on excellent customer service.  That was actually one of their selling points for DAoC.  "You pay more, but you get more."  As a matter of fact, that was one of the things that sold me.  I was sick and tired of Verant's BS, and after trying Anarchy Online, HA! Don't even get me started on their service. Informing the player base about certain changes is part of customer service.<br>
<br>
